# Phase 1 — MVP Core — Implementation Plan

> Build a working group creation flow, project brief submission, AI task assignment using BYOK keys, and a basic task board.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Schema design review needed before migration.** The database schema below defines all 6 models for Phase 1. Please review the field names, types, relations, and enums before I run `prisma migrate dev`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Circular relation decision:** The spec says `Group.projectBriefId` points to `ProjectBrief`, but `ProjectBrief.groupId` also points back to `Group`. This creates a circular FK dependency that Prisma handles poorly. My proposed solution: **drop `Group.projectBriefId`** and access the brief via the reverse relation `group.projectBrief` (one-to-one from ProjectBrief side). The group dashboard queries the brief through `ProjectBrief.where({ groupId })` — same result, cleaner schema.

> [!WARNING]
> **shadcn/ui CLI requires specific setup.** I'll use `npx shadcn@latest init` after the Next.js project is scaffolded, then install components individually (`button`, `input`, `textarea`, `select`, `dialog`, `badge`, `skeleton`, `toast`, `card`, `dropdown-menu`, `radio-group`, `calendar`, `popover`, `label`, `separator`).

## Open Questions

1. **Multiple groups per user?** The spec allows a user to be a `GroupMember` in many groups. Is that correct for Phase 1, or should we limit to one active group?
2. **Self-join prevention?** Should the group creator automatically be added as a `GroupMember` when they create the group? I'm assuming **yes** — the creator is member #1.
3. **Skill profile enforcement?** The spec says "prompt user to complete their skill profile after joining." Should this be a **hard block** (redirect to `/dashboard/profile/setup` until completed) or a **soft prompt** (dismissible banner)?

